  "market_context": "Uptrend in gold (XAUUSD) on the 1-hour chart, following a strong impulsive move from a swing low to a swing high, then a pullback to a second swing low, setting up the first measured move extension.",
  "key_observation": "Price rallied to the 1.0 (100% measured move) and 1.618 Fibonacci extension levels and sold off sharply at both, confirming them as high-probability resistance targets.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst selected the Trend-Based Fibonacci Extension tool (not retracement) and simplified settings to show only levels 0, 1, and 1.618.",
    "Step 2: Anchored the Fib extension at the first swing low, then the swing high, then the next swing low to define the measured move baseline.",
    "Step 3: Dragged the extension to the right to project forward targets, identifying the 1.0 level (100% of the prior swing) as the first key resistance zone.",
    "Step 4: Observed price reaching the 1.0 level and selling off, confirming it as a valid profit-taking zone.",
    "Step 5: Noted that price also rejected the 1.618 extension level later, reinforcing its significance as a secondary target resistance."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price sold off at both the 1.0 and 1.618 Fib extension levels; no explicit trade entry/exit was described, only price reaction confirmation.",
  "lessons": "The 1.0 and 1.618 Fibonacci extension levels—derived from a clean swing low–high–low sequence—serve as reliable resistance targets in trending markets; simplifying Fib settings improves clarity for target identification.",
